political order grappled with the endemic uncertainties induced by dynastic bodies. By following the day-to-day practices of knowledge making in response to the unpredictability of royal health, the book shows how the ruling family’s mortal coils regularly threatened to destabilize the institutionalized legal fiction of kingship. Dynastic politics was not only as a transitory stage of state formation, part of elite cooperation, or a cultural construct. It needs to be approached through everyday practices that put ailing dynastic bodies front and center. In a period of intensifying political planning, it constituted one of the most important sites for changing the political itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 4aDynastische Krise. 4aFrühe Neuzeit. 4aKörperlichkeit. 4aPolitik. 7aHISTORY / Modern / 17th Century.2bisacsh  aDynastic crisis.  acorporeality.  aearly modern period.  apolitics.0 cEPUBz97831107446510 cprintz978311074452140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311074460640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110744606423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110744606/original  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK